text: The King of Corsica was the ruler of the island of Corsica, located in the Mediterranean Sea from March 1736 to 1796. Theodore of Corsica (March 1736 – November 1736) Colonel Frederick (11 December 1756-1797) (Head of House von Neuhoff (claimed) George III (1794–1796) Anglo-Corsican Kingdom The kingdom ended in 1796. Category:History of Corsica
title: King of Corsica
